# calc_semantic_cancellation.numos — exact fraction cancellation: 1/2 + 1/2 == 1.
#
# Phase 8C semantic smoke. NO screenshot, NO golden.
#
# Two fractions summed to an exact integer. Each 1/2 is built with the fraction
# key (FRAC) and exited with RIGHT; the exact rational engine adds them to 2/2 and
# reduces to the integer 1 (formatExactVal renders "1", not "1/1").
#
# Run: program --headless --deterministic --script <this> --frames 1400 --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 parse · 3 screenshot · 4 assertion failure.

log "calc_semantic_cancellation: waiting for launcher"
wait 200
open_app Calculation
wait 60

key 1
key FRAC
key 2
key RIGHT
key +
key 1
key FRAC
key 2
key RIGHT
key ENTER
wait 120

assert_app Calculation
assert_no_error
assert_result 1
log "calc_semantic_cancellation: PASS (1/2 + 1/2 == 1)"
